    "Comprising seven open-source English legal datasets, the LexGLUE dataset involves tasks categorized into multi-label classification, multi-class classification, and multiple choice Q&A.",
    "• LEXTREME (Niklaus et al, 2023).",
    "Comprising 11 evaluation sub-datasets spanning 24 languages, the LEXTREME dataset categorizes all evaluation content into 18 tasks, such as Brazilian court decisions, German argument mining, Greek legal code, Swiss judgment prediction, among others.",
    "• SCALE (Rasiah et al, 2023).",
    "The evaluation content of the SCALE dataset originates from diverse legal NLP datasets within the Swiss legal system and additional datasets, exploring research aspects related to five languages and the federal legal framework."
